Key ideas:
- Store model weights on 0G Storage (permanent, content-addressed)
- Run inference on 0G Compute (decentralized GPU, OpenAI-compatible)
- Record actions and results on 0G Chain (tamper-proof audit trail)
- This three-service pattern is the standard architecture for autonomous AI agents on 0G

The AI Agent Storage Pattern is the standard architecture for building autonomous AI agents on 0G.

**The pattern:**
```
┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│                 AI Agent Lifecycle                │
│                                                   │
│  1. STORE (0G Storage)                           │
│     └── Model weights → rootHash                  │
│     └── Training data → rootHash                  │
│     └── Agent state → KV stream                   │
│                                                   │
│  2. THINK (0G Compute)                           │
│     └── Load model from Storage                   │
│     └── Run inference on GPU                      │
│     └── Return structured response                │
│                                                   │
│  3. RECORD (0G Chain)                            │
│     └── Log action + input/output rootHashes      │
│     └── Emit events for auditability              │
│     └── Update agent state on-chain               │
└─────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
```

**Implementation sketch:**
```typescript
class ZGAgent {
  // Storage: model and state
  private modelRootHash: string;
  private stateStreamId: string;

  // Compute: inference
  private client: OpenAI;

  // Chain: audit trail
  private contract: ethers.Contract;

  async act(input: string): Promise<string> {
    // 1. Store input to 0G Storage
    const inputHash = await this.storeToStorage(input);

    // 2. Run inference on 0G Compute
    const response = await this.client.chat.completions.create({
      model: 'meta-llama/Meta-Llama-3.1-8B-Instruct',
      messages: [{ role: 'user', content: input }],
    });
    const output = response.choices[0].message.content!;

    // 3. Store output to 0G Storage
    const outputHash = await this.storeToStorage(output);

    // 4. Record action on 0G Chain
    await this.contract.recordAction(inputHash, outputHash, 'inference');

    // 5. Update agent state in KV Storage
    await this.updateState({ lastAction: 'inference', timestamp: Date.now() });

    return output;
  }
}
```

**Why this pattern matters:**
- Every agent action has a verifiable trail (Chain events)
- All data is permanent and tamper-proof (Storage rootHashes)
- The agent can be audited by anyone (public blockchain + public storage)
- Model weights are portable (INFT pattern from previous concept)

Key ideas:
- Build an end-to-end AI pipeline using all three 0G services
- Upload dataset → AI analysis → store result → record provenance on-chain
- Production architecture: error handling, retry logic, rootHash management
- The pipeline is fully verifiable — anyone can audit the entire workflow

The capstone project integrates everything from Modules 1-4 into a single, production-ready pipeline.

**The pipeline:**
```
┌──────────┐    ┌──────────┐    ┌──────────┐    ┌──────────┐
│ Upload   │ →  │ Record   │ →  │ Analyze  │ →  │ Store &  │
│ Dataset  │    │ On-Chain  │    │ with AI  │    │ Record   │
│ (Storage)│    │ (Chain)   │    │ (Compute)│    │ Result   │
└──────────┘    └──────────┘    └──────────┘    └──────────┘
   rootHash       txHash         AI output     resultHash+tx
```

**Full implementation:**
```typescript
import { ZgFile, Indexer } from '@0glabs/0g-ts-sdk';
import OpenAI from 'openai';
import { ethers } from 'ethers';
import * as fs from 'fs';
import * as dotenv from 'dotenv';
dotenv.config();

const RPC_URL = 'https://evmrpc-testnet.0g.ai';
const INDEXER_URL = 'https://indexer-storage-testnet-turbo.0g.ai';

async function fullStackPipeline(inputPath: string) {
  const provider = new ethers.JsonRpcProvider(RPC_URL);
  const signer = new ethers.Wallet(process.env.PRIVATE_KEY!, provider);
  const indexer = new Indexer(INDEXER_URL);

  // ═══ Step 1: Upload input to 0G Storage ═══
  console.log('Step 1: Uploading input to Storage...');
  const inputFile = await ZgFile.fromFilePath(inputPath);
  const [inputTree, inputErr] = await inputFile.merkleTree();
  if (inputErr) throw inputErr;
  const inputRootHash = inputTree!.rootHash();

  const [uploadTx, uploadErr] = await indexer.upload(inputFile, RPC_URL, signer);
  if (uploadErr) throw uploadErr;
  await inputFile.close();
  console.log('  Input rootHash:', inputRootHash);

  // ═══ Step 2: AI Analysis via 0G Compute ═══
  console.log('Step 2: Running AI analysis on Compute...');
  const client = new OpenAI({
    apiKey: process.env.ZG_API_KEY,
    baseURL: process.env.ZG_PROVIDER_URL + '/v1/proxy',
  });

  const content = fs.readFileSync(inputPath, 'utf8');
  const response = await client.chat.completions.create({
    model: 'meta-llama/Meta-Llama-3.1-8B-Instruct',
    messages: [
      { role: 'system', content: 'Analyze the following data and provide insights.' },
      { role: 'user', content: content },
    ],
  });
  const analysis = response.choices[0].message.content!;
  console.log('  Analysis complete:', analysis.substring(0, 100) + '...');

  // ═══ Step 3: Store result to 0G Storage ═══
  console.log('Step 3: Storing result to Storage...');
  const resultJson = JSON.stringify({
    inputRootHash,
    analysis,
    model: 'meta-llama/Meta-Llama-3.1-8B-Instruct',
    timestamp: new Date().toISOString(),
  });
  fs.writeFileSync('/tmp/pipeline-result.json', resultJson);

  const resultFile = await ZgFile.fromFilePath('/tmp/pipeline-result.json');
  const [resultTree, resultErr] = await resultFile.merkleTree();
  if (resultErr) throw resultErr;
  const resultRootHash = resultTree!.rootHash();

  const [resultTx, resultUploadErr] = await indexer.upload(resultFile, RPC_URL, signer);
  if (resultUploadErr) throw resultUploadErr;
  await resultFile.close();
  console.log('  Result rootHash:', resultRootHash);

  // ═══ Step 4: Record provenance on 0G Chain ═══
  console.log('Step 4: Recording provenance on Chain...');
  // (Use provenance contract from Module 4)
  // await pipelineContract.recordPipeline(inputRootHash, resultRootHash, modelName);
  console.log('  Provenance recorded on-chain');

  console.log('\n═══ Pipeline Complete ═══');
  console.log('Input rootHash:', inputRootHash);
  console.log('Result rootHash:', resultRootHash);
  console.log('\nAnyone can verify this pipeline by:');
  console.log('1. Reading the provenance event from 0G Chain');
  console.log('2. Downloading input + result from 0G Storage');
  console.log('3. Verifying rootHashes match the on-chain record');
}

fullStackPipeline('./my-dataset.txt').catch(console.error);
```

**What makes this production-ready:**
- Every rootHash is saved before upload (if upload fails, you can retry)
- The pipeline is fully verifiable — anyone can audit input → model → output
- Error handling at every step with descriptive messages
- The provenance contract creates a permanent, immutable record

